Kiambu government will set up a solid waste recycling plant to manage disposal.Environment executive Esther Njuguna said the plant will serve Kiambu, Thika and Limuru. She spoke on Wednesday at Gioto, the county s second largest dumpsite. Every day people produce garbage which is dumped at this site, she said.Njuguna said the plant will also provide jobs for the youth. Kiambu residents have been complaining about smoke when the garbage is burnt.They will hold a peaceful demonstration on Monday to press the county to move the dumpsite away from residential areas. Resident David Mwaniki said, On Sunday, the Catholic and PCEA churches could not hold services because of the stench and smoke from the site. 